The paper deals with information theoretic measures and their application to structure discovery, which is a common topic in machine learning and statistics. The use of Markov factor graph models and nonparametric models also suggests a focus on learning and inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of statistical validation and hypothesis testing suggests a possible fit with cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
